      "step_id": "57c04402",
      "step_index": 1,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "- **Core scaffold:** substituted **benzene (one aromatic ring)**.\n- **Substituents / functional groups:**\n  - **Methyl** on the ring (adds modest lipophilicity).\n  - **Two carboxylic acids**: one directly on the ring (**benzoic acid**-like), and one on a side chain (**\u03b1-amino acid carboxylate**).\n  - **Primary amine** on the benzylic stereocenter (**\u2013CH(NH2)\u2013CO2H**).\n- **Ionization / charge state at pH 7.4 (qualitative):**\n  - Carboxylic acids (pKa ~2\u20135) \u2192 largely **deprotonated (\u2013COO\u207b)**.\n  - Primary amine (pKa often ~9\u201310, but can be lowered by nearby carboxylate) \u2192 largely **protonated (\u2013NH3\u207a)**.\n  - Net: likely **zwitterionic**, often with **overall ~\u20131 to 0** depending on micro-pKa.\n- **Structural alerts for CYP2D6 inhibition:**\n  - Has a **basic N**, but it is a **primary amine** in a highly polar/zwitterionic context.\n  - Lacks **tertiary amine** / \u201cquinidine-like\u201d bulky cationic-lipophilic motif.",
      "tool_name": null,
