      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### 3) CONSIDER mechanistic basis (interaction with CYP2D6)\nMechanistically, inhibition often involves:\n- **Anchoring of a protonated amine** to an acidic site (Asp301) and positioning near the heme.\n- **Hydrophobic/aromatic interactions** that stabilize the complex and block substrate access.",
